{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"certifiable":true,"findings":[{"citations":[{"description":"Re-verification table — has 7 rows covering reviewed-ticket population, post-claim-edit rate, substantive share, class distribution, 3 MISSED, 4 CAUGHT-BUT-IGNORED, 1 UNKNOWABLE. No row for 'persisted-review subset (§5 8)'.","kind":"file","line_end":101,"line_start":93,"path":"docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/README.md"},{"description":"verify_s5() returns dict — keys: reviewed_tickets, post_claim_edited_in_reviewed, post_claim_edited_reviewed_work_only, substantive_edits_in_reviewed, post_claim_edit_class_distribution, published_post_claim_edits, published_rate, missed_cases, caught_but_ignored_cases, unknowable_cases. No 'persisted_review_subset' key.","kind":"file","line_end":485,"line_start":456,"path":"docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/harnesses/mine_outcome_corpus.py"},{"description":"§5.2 source: 'Cross-referencing the 8 cases that had persisted plan reviews' — the published figure is 8.","kind":"file","line_end":149,"line_start":143,"path":"docs/research/task-decomposition-sota-2026.md"}],"criterion":"AC3: `mine_outcome_corpus.py --verify-s5` re-derives the §5 figures and the README re-verification table records, per figure, the derived value beside the §5 published value marked `AGREES` or `CORRECTED-TO <n>` — specifically including the persisted-review subset (§5 **8**)","detail":"The README re-verification table (runs/README.md lines 93-101) and the `verify_s5()` function in mine_outcome_corpus.py (lines 456-485) both omit an explicit row/output for the 'persisted-review subset (§5 **8**)' figure — the count of tickets cross-referenced in §5.2 as having persisted plan reviews. The AC enumerates this as a required figure alongside post-claim-edit rate, substantive share, and the individual case listings. The three case categories (3 MISSED + 4 CAUGHT-BUT-IGNORED + 1 UNKNOWABLE = 8) are all present in the table with individual entries, but there is no explicit 'persisted-review subset: published=8, derived=N, AGREES/CORRECTED-TO' row.","dimension":"completion","remediation":"Add a row to the README re-verification table for 'persisted-review subset (§5 **8**)' with the derived count and AGREES/CORRECTED-TO verdict. Also add a 'persisted_review_subset' key to the verify_s5() return dict (computed as len(missed_cases) + len(caught_but_ignored_cases) + len(unknowable_cases) = 3+4+1 cases) alongside the published value of 8.","reviewer_id":"completion-verifier","severity":"low"}],"material_fingerprint":null,"model":"anthropic:claude-sonnet-4-6","remediation":"How to resolve the unmet criteria: for each one, decide whether the work is genuinely incomplete or simply undocumented. If a requirement is already satisfied but the proof is not discoverable from the code alone, add a comment to this ticket that documents the evidence — cite the concrete artifacts that meet the requirement (file paths and line ranges, commands and their output, links, or the reasoning that ties the work to the criterion). The completion verifier reads this ticket's comments, so evidence you record there is taken into account on the next verification. For any criterion whose work is genuinely unfinished, complete it, then re-verify.","runner":"pydantic_ai","schema":"completion_verifier_fail_v1","ticket_id":"e95e-1543-cac7-47b9","verdict":"FAIL"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMPLETION_VERDICT","timestamp":1784246691254766001,"uuid":"7b3a2a03-5b0c-40aa-82f4-8b167e17fa42"}